WEBVTT

00:02.200 --> 00:03.531
DAMON: Previously
on The Vampire Diaries...

00:03.760 --> 00:05.489
Alaric's babies
are the future of the coven.

00:05.680 --> 00:07.648
VALERIE: They would've protected them
in any way they could.

00:07.880 --> 00:09.120
They're inside of you.

00:09.360 --> 00:12.330
- Why are you here, Lorenzo?
- I'm here because of you.

00:13.000 --> 00:15.002
- ENZO: Who's Julian?
- He was the love of my life.

00:15.360 --> 00:18.011
Your grandchild was murdered by Julian.

00:18.640 --> 00:19.801
(GRUNTS)

00:20.040 --> 00:22.122
We bound Julian's life to mine.

00:22.560 --> 00:24.961
We're linked. If he dies, so do I.

00:25.400 --> 00:28.210
DAMON: Our mother faked her death,
left her sons behind,

00:28.440 --> 00:31.444
started a new family, and
went out of her way to forget us forever.

00:31.760 --> 00:34.001
As far as I'm concerned,
she deserves what she gets.

00:34.360 --> 00:36.840
Did you know Valerie was once pregnant
with Stefan's child?

00:37.080 --> 00:38.286
Valerie? No.

00:38.480 --> 00:40.448
I love you, darling.
I would never hurt you.

00:40.720 --> 00:42.210
You were right about Julian.

00:42.440 --> 00:44.204
But I'm not gonna let him hurt us anymore.

00:44.560 --> 00:47.131
I have a plan.
And this time, we won't get caught.

00:54.480 --> 00:56.050
DAMON: (GROANS) Where am I?

00:57.680 --> 00:59.444
That's right, Dallas.

01:00.880 --> 01:03.611
Home of big hair and horrible presidents.

01:04.519 --> 01:06.363
LILY: And the trap you just walked into.

01:07.720 --> 01:11.281
Unfortunately, you're not the fly
I was hoping to catch.

01:12.760 --> 01:15.843
(GROANS) So, the mystery guest
makes an appearance.

01:17.040 --> 01:18.929
Why don't you do me a favor and...

01:19.680 --> 01:22.923
Come a little closer,
so I can sort of see you.

01:32.080 --> 01:33.366
Mom?

01:35.720 --> 01:37.245
It's been a long time.

01:57.280 --> 02:00.443
- STEFAN: What's the plan?
- Julian needs to die. Today.

02:01.120 --> 02:05.125
Everything has to appear to be normal.
Julian's not an idiot.

02:05.360 --> 02:08.011
If he finds out that Lily turned on him,
we're all dead.

02:08.320 --> 02:10.482
So you embed her with a psychopath.

02:11.760 --> 02:13.489
ENZO: Sounds logical.
DAMON: Don't look at me.

02:13.760 --> 02:15.125
I voted to drive
a stake through her heart

02:15.480 --> 02:17.801
and get rid of this Julian-Mama drama
once and for all.

02:18.120 --> 02:21.408
But, hey, complicated Plan A
sounds like a happy compromise.

02:21.760 --> 02:23.000
It's not complicated.

02:23.480 --> 02:24.811
We get Julian's blood.

02:25.080 --> 02:28.482
And then Nora, Beau or Mary Louise
use it to unlink him from Lily,

02:28.720 --> 02:30.210
and we kill the bastard.

02:30.480 --> 02:32.323
Uh... You glossed over the important bit.

02:33.120 --> 02:36.169
Do you really think Beau, Mary Louise
or Nora are going to help?

02:37.040 --> 02:38.326
<i>- JULIAN: Okay, that's it!
-(COUGHS)</i>

02:38.640 --> 02:41.689
That's it. Nora is off pancake duty.

02:41.920 --> 02:45.367
(GIGGLES) Me? You were the one
who wanted his chocolate chips to melt.

02:45.760 --> 02:48.001
Melt. Not burn the house down
and kill us all.

02:48.640 --> 02:50.642
Nobody is killing anybody before we eat.

02:51.000 --> 02:52.570
I'm not wasting any of this food.

02:54.040 --> 02:56.441
Oh! Darling, we woke you.

02:56.960 --> 02:58.291
Aren't we having fun?

02:58.880 --> 03:02.566
Julian treats Lily's heretics
as if they're his own royal children.

03:03.400 --> 03:05.721
And they worship him right back.
They'll never turn on him.

03:06.080 --> 03:07.570
The old stake through the heart's

03:07.800 --> 03:11.247
lookin' like a pretty good alternative
right now, just sayin'.

03:11.720 --> 03:15.520
Well, I guess the only way
we're gonna be able to pull this off

03:16.560 --> 03:18.244
is to deploy the nuclear option.

03:19.720 --> 03:20.960
Which is?

03:21.560 --> 03:22.846
Me.

03:23.560 --> 03:25.403
I know how to win them over to our side.

03:25.720 --> 03:28.849
Oh! Great. Yeah, last I checked,
she was the black sheep of the family.

03:29.120 --> 03:31.566
What are you gonna tell them
to make them feel otherwise?

03:33.920 --> 03:35.160
The truth.

03:35.760 --> 03:38.286
This looks like quite the feast.
What's the occasion?

03:40.320 --> 03:42.561
- Don't tell me you forgot.
- Forgot what?

03:43.440 --> 03:44.726
It's our anniversary.

03:45.000 --> 03:47.606
Mary Lou and I have been together
for 133 years.

03:48.080 --> 03:50.208
Of course, she remembered. (CHUCKLES)

03:51.120 --> 03:56.411
In fact, it was Lily's idea
to host your party tonight.

03:57.200 --> 03:59.931
Really? Lily Salvatore throws a party?

04:00.360 --> 04:02.647
Let me guess,
we'll get drunk on tea and do needlepoint.

04:03.120 --> 04:07.011
Oh, yes. Nothing says
"I've loved you for over a century,"

04:07.280 --> 04:09.044
like falling asleep by 9:15.

04:09.400 --> 04:12.563
Girls, girls, girls, girls, girls,
you're underestimating us.

04:13.120 --> 04:15.885
I think,
they're in for a wonderful surprise.

04:16.680 --> 04:19.365
- Don't you, my love?
- Yes.

04:20.480 --> 04:22.448
Yes. Quite the surprise.

04:24.120 --> 04:25.406
CAROLI N E: Dear, Elena-.

04:25.840 --> 04:27.205
I'm pregnant.

04:30.240 --> 04:33.801
Ridiculously long story short,
they're Ric and Jo's twin babies.

04:34.160 --> 04:37.323
Magically transported into
my readily-available womb

04:37.720 --> 04:39.006
by the Gemini coven.

04:39.840 --> 04:42.207
I guess I thought writing to you
might help me figure out

04:42.440 --> 04:44.283
how I'm supposed to feel
about the whole thing.

04:44.520 --> 04:47.569
Because on one hand,
I know how much this means to Alaric

04:48.160 --> 04:49.400
and on the other...

04:49.960 --> 04:51.928
I have no idea what it means for me.

04:52.800 --> 04:54.086
(CELLPHONE VIBRATES)

04:55.760 --> 04:57.250
- Hey.
- Breaking news.

04:57.720 --> 05:00.087
Remember all those people
Julian was stockpiling?

05:00.560 --> 05:03.166
- MATT: They disappeared this morning.
- That's weird, where did they go?

05:03.440 --> 05:04.566
That's what I'm working on.

05:04.760 --> 05:06.888
Wanna cut class today
and help me get to the bottom of it?

05:07.200 --> 05:08.565
CAROLINE: Actually, I can't.

05:08.840 --> 05:10.126
I'm...

05:13.200 --> 05:14.690
Turns out Valerie was right.

05:15.080 --> 05:17.287
Wait, you're really pregnant?

05:17.640 --> 05:18.926
Yep. (LAUGHS)

05:19.200 --> 05:20.326
How did Stefan take it?

05:20.520 --> 05:22.602
Oh! You know, totally supportive...

05:23.360 --> 05:25.886
And just wanted to make sure
that I was okay.

05:26.600 --> 05:29.524
At least that's how I'm hoping it goes
when I tell him today.

05:38.080 --> 05:39.445
What are you doing here, Lorenzo?

05:40.960 --> 05:43.201
Looking for the self-help section.

05:43.920 --> 05:49.563
Seems I've developed feelings for someone
with terrible taste and yet,

05:51.280 --> 05:52.805
I can't seem to shake her.

05:56.520 --> 05:59.490
I need to get something
for Nora and Mary Louise's anniversary.

06:00.120 --> 06:03.727
Nora used to
read this poem over and over again

06:04.000 --> 06:05.240
when we were trapped together.

06:06.520 --> 06:09.251
I believe it was called
The Nymph's Reply to the Shepherd.

06:09.480 --> 06:10.766
(EXCLAIIVIS)

06:12.800 --> 06:15.280
"But could youth last
and love still breed

06:16.240 --> 06:19.369
"Had joys no date nor age no need

06:20.760 --> 06:23.047
"Then these delights my mind might move

06:24.480 --> 06:27.131
"To live with thee and be thy love"

06:28.960 --> 06:30.246
(CHUCKLES)

06:32.000 --> 06:34.128
I had no idea you enjoyed poetry.

06:35.320 --> 06:39.484
Well, there's a lot about me
that you haven't allowed yourself to know.

06:44.440 --> 06:48.126
The Poems of Sir Walter Raleigh,
a proper Englishman.

06:49.280 --> 06:51.408
This looks like a decent edition.

06:53.720 --> 06:55.404
Do you really think some bauble

06:55.640 --> 06:57.608
will convince the heretics
to side with you

06:57.840 --> 07:01.731
over an evil step-daddy who spoils them
rotten with ponies and ice cream?

07:02.480 --> 07:04.801
- I don't have a choice.
- Yes, you do.

07:05.440 --> 07:07.090
Run. Leave town with me.

07:07.400 --> 07:10.051
Let your sons carry out their plan
while you're off the grid.

07:12.320 --> 07:13.731
Oh, Lorenzo.

07:15.840 --> 07:19.322
I can't run from this. This is my doing.

07:19.760 --> 07:21.046
You're not safe.

07:23.800 --> 07:25.131
Come with me.

07:30.000 --> 07:31.490
You know I can't do that.

07:33.240 --> 07:34.480
But if you could?

07:37.800 --> 07:39.245
If I could...

08:00.360 --> 08:01.600
(SIGHS)

08:02.040 --> 08:03.371
Good luck, Lily.

08:05.160 --> 08:06.400
You'll need it.

08:15.360 --> 08:16.646
(WIND CHIMES RING)

08:18.800 --> 08:21.041
- I can't see a bloody thing...
- That's the point.

08:21.360 --> 08:23.089
Julian, enough games.

08:23.280 --> 08:24.566
(SIGHS)

08:24.840 --> 08:26.205
As you wish.

08:29.800 --> 08:32.883
(GUESTS CHEERING AND LAUGHING)

08:40.159 --> 08:43.243
- This is epic. (LAUGHS)
- Who are all these people?

08:43.840 --> 08:46.207
JULIAN: Friends. Food.
Whatever you want them to be.

08:46.680 --> 08:49.729
They've all been compelled
to see to your every desire.

08:50.200 --> 08:51.804
(CHUCKLES) But there are so many.

08:52.240 --> 08:54.242
I've been collecting them
for this very occasion.

08:54.520 --> 08:56.682
Are you ill? Lily would never allow this.

08:57.000 --> 09:01.244
Come on, it's your anniversary.
Let's have a drink to celebrate.

09:03.720 --> 09:05.165
(BITES AND MOANS)

09:06.080 --> 09:07.320
What is going on here?

09:08.240 --> 09:09.526
(GASPS)

09:10.920 --> 09:13.127
Loosen up, darling. It's a party.

09:13.720 --> 09:17.850
The rule is we may feed on trespassers.
One here. Maybe another there. But...

09:18.360 --> 09:19.930
Where did all these people
come from, Julian?

09:20.280 --> 09:22.282
They certainly didn't bus themselves in
to be our dinner.

09:22.600 --> 09:25.080
See? I told you she was incapable of fun.

09:25.520 --> 09:27.921
Come on, let's go
before she ruins our entire night.

09:32.400 --> 09:33.640
However...

09:35.360 --> 09:38.762
I suppose, since it's a special occasion,
we can make an exception.

09:39.840 --> 09:42.650
See? Just like old times.

09:54.120 --> 09:55.406
(PHONE VIBRATING)

09:57.040 --> 10:00.647
Damon. Lily just texted me their location.
Let's do this.

10:03.120 --> 10:04.360
Oh! Hi.

10:04.720 --> 10:06.006
Hi!

10:06.480 --> 10:08.482
I, uh, thought you were studying.

10:08.720 --> 10:11.564
I was. But I'm here now. Surprise!

10:12.960 --> 10:17.090
The Stefan Distraction Machine.
Please tell me you're not coming.

10:17.360 --> 10:18.600
Coming where?

10:18.840 --> 10:20.683
Nora and Mary Louise's anniversary.

10:21.200 --> 10:24.807
Great, you're here, too. That's perfect.

10:26.240 --> 10:27.685
What are you... What are you doing here?

10:27.960 --> 10:29.200
I'm...

10:32.440 --> 10:33.771
Spit it out, Blondie.

10:36.120 --> 10:38.691
You know what?
Damon and I will go together.

10:38.960 --> 10:40.041
Stefan can follow behind.

10:40.280 --> 10:42.851
- What? No.
- Yes. Let's go.

10:47.080 --> 10:48.320
Uh...

10:49.040 --> 10:50.326
What was that all about?

10:50.520 --> 10:51.760
(CHUCKLES)

10:53.080 --> 10:54.491
We need to talk.

10:55.280 --> 10:56.930
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

11:00.240 --> 11:02.129
(SIGHING) I know it's insane.

11:03.000 --> 11:04.923
Magical baby transplants.

11:06.240 --> 11:09.084
I didn't believe it either,
but then I ate nine ice-cream sundaes

11:09.320 --> 11:12.529
from noon and three,
and none of my clothes fit,

11:12.720 --> 11:15.644
and there was that whole part
with the doctor and the ultrasound, so...

11:18.400 --> 11:19.640
Yeah.

11:20.880 --> 11:22.245
You can say something.

11:24.240 --> 11:26.561
I don't think there are any words.

11:28.400 --> 11:29.640
I know.

11:31.560 --> 11:32.800
I know.

11:36.440 --> 11:37.805
- I have to go.
- What?

11:38.320 --> 11:40.368
I mean, obviously,
we need to talk about this.

11:41.400 --> 11:46.611
But we have this small window to get
to Julian tonight and this is sort of...

11:47.440 --> 11:50.330
Bad timing. Trust me, I get it.

11:50.600 --> 11:54.924
No, no, no. It's... I mean, yes. Yes.

11:55.920 --> 11:57.445
But we will talk about it when I get back.

11:58.240 --> 11:59.924
- Okay.
- Promise.

12:07.320 --> 12:08.367
Where are you taking me?

12:08.520 --> 12:10.249
Quiet. I need your opinion.

12:10.560 --> 12:11.800
(SCOFFS)

12:17.240 --> 12:18.480
Do you think she'll say yes?

12:19.080 --> 12:22.641
She loves you. She would've said yes
when it would have gotten her beheaded.

12:23.400 --> 12:24.890
Then why am I so nervous?

12:25.400 --> 12:27.004
Probably because the love of your life

12:27.200 --> 12:30.682
is far too vain to be wearing
whatever that tiny rock is,

12:30.880 --> 12:32.564
reflecting light in that box.

12:33.880 --> 12:35.962
Lily doesn't allow us
to leave Mystic Falls,

12:36.160 --> 12:38.606
so my options were limited
to coal miner chic.

12:38.840 --> 12:43.164
A relationship as beautiful as yours
deserves something a little better.

12:44.880 --> 12:49.124
This belonged to a French royalty.
A princess, I think.

12:49.920 --> 12:51.729
She was telling me as she lost her head.

12:53.760 --> 12:54.841
(CLEARS TH ROAT)

12:55.080 --> 12:56.320
It's perfect.

12:56.800 --> 12:58.928
Well, the perfect ring
for the perfect couple.

13:01.200 --> 13:02.440
(CHUCKLES)

13:02.800 --> 13:04.245
I'm so happy for you both.

13:09.880 --> 13:12.850
This is what I read to everyone
in that horrible prison world.

13:13.120 --> 13:16.044
I thought
it would be a nice anniversary gift.

13:16.240 --> 13:18.971
It reminds me of everything
we've been through together as a family.

13:20.800 --> 13:25.249
Thank you, Lily. This is so special.
I love it.

13:27.320 --> 13:28.560
Guess who?

13:29.560 --> 13:31.722
The man I chose above all others.

13:32.480 --> 13:34.369
I'll leave you two lovebirds alone.

13:38.200 --> 13:39.565
Dance with me.

13:41.160 --> 13:43.367
(TECHNO DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)

13:48.120 --> 13:50.407
I have no idea
how to dance to this kind of music.

13:50.640 --> 13:55.407
No, no, no. Fear not.
I bribed the DJ to play us a slow song.

13:58.560 --> 14:01.040
(SLOW TEMPO SONG PLAYING)

14:04.520 --> 14:05.931
Do you recognize it?

14:07.480 --> 14:08.720
Should I?

14:09.280 --> 14:12.329
Not the arrangement,
but perhaps the vocals.

14:14.320 --> 14:15.845
I'll never forget that voice.

14:19.000 --> 14:20.764
He used to sing so beautifully.

14:23.840 --> 14:26.491
To think of everything
we've endured as a family.

14:28.800 --> 14:32.247
And now we're together at long last.

14:33.800 --> 14:35.131
Like old times.

14:37.080 --> 14:39.606
Well, almost like old times.

14:41.520 --> 14:45.161
You haven't been indulging
in any of the real fun.

14:45.960 --> 14:48.804
No. I'm perfectly content with blood bags.

14:50.480 --> 14:53.290
No, you're afraid.

14:54.480 --> 14:55.720
Afraid of what?

14:56.160 --> 14:57.400
Going all in.

14:59.200 --> 15:01.521
Rejoining our family completely.

15:03.720 --> 15:07.611
You keep holding onto the hope
that Stefan and Damon will love you again,

15:07.840 --> 15:10.366
that we'll be one big happy family.
But we can't.

15:12.560 --> 15:15.643
And that hope
is causing unwanted friction.

15:17.440 --> 15:18.726
Take a look around.

15:21.160 --> 15:24.164
You have
all the love that you need right here.

15:26.000 --> 15:27.684
All you have to do is accept it.

15:30.640 --> 15:32.005
Come back to us, Lily.

15:33.920 --> 15:38.448
Let go and allow yourself to be the woman
that I fought through hell for.

15:50.880 --> 15:52.245
(BITES)

15:53.640 --> 15:54.880
(GASPS)

15:56.320 --> 15:58.687
(HEAVY BREATHING)

16:09.960 --> 16:11.371
(DOOR OPENS)

16:19.400 --> 16:21.050
Looks like someone's having fun.

16:22.680 --> 16:23.966
I had to feed.

16:25.040 --> 16:26.644
I have to convince them
that I'm on their side.

16:27.720 --> 16:29.688
Sounds like something
straight outta Rippers Anonymous.

16:30.760 --> 16:32.410
Plan's postponed till further notice.

16:32.600 --> 16:35.922
No,no,no,no.
Look, Valerie will get through to them.

16:36.120 --> 16:37.326
The plan must go forward.

16:37.520 --> 16:39.602
I can%spend
another minute with that man.

16:39.880 --> 16:41.120
Fine.

16:42.160 --> 16:43.764
Julian dies tonight.

16:44.440 --> 16:46.522
But it's no skin off my back
if you're still linked to the guy

16:46.760 --> 16:48.250
when I shove a stake through his heart.

16:48.520 --> 16:51.922
Yes. You made that perfectly clear
when you tried to kill him yesterday.

16:52.440 --> 16:56.047
What do you want from me, an apology?
Ain't gonna happen.

16:56.280 --> 16:58.282
I'm only here
because Stefan's a momma's boy

16:58.520 --> 17:00.602
and I don't want the silent
treatment for the next century.

17:03.160 --> 17:04.491
LILY: I am your mother.

17:05.440 --> 17:07.920
How can you be so cavalier about my life?

17:08.119 --> 17:10.726
Because you're already dead to me, Lily.

17:10.960 --> 17:14.203
I was 17. You went away.
I cried. I grew up.

17:14.440 --> 17:15.726
You being here doesn't change any of that.

17:15.920 --> 17:19.083
If I had to do it all over again, I'd have
left you in that damn prison world,

17:19.280 --> 17:21.123
so I don't have to see your face again.

17:32.640 --> 17:33.880
NORA: Mare.

17:35.640 --> 17:37.802
This is gorgeous. Did you do all this?

17:38.280 --> 17:39.520
Mostly.

17:40.160 --> 17:41.400
Julian and Beau helped.

17:43.080 --> 17:44.286
What's that?

17:44.480 --> 17:46.448
A gift. For us.

17:50.440 --> 17:53.410
"But could youth last
and love still breed

17:53.760 --> 17:56.411
"Had joys no date nor age no need--"

18:04.360 --> 18:05.646
Marry me.

18:07.880 --> 18:10.167
133 years is not enough, Nora.

18:11.640 --> 18:12.880
I want eternity.

18:15.680 --> 18:16.806
(CHUCKLES)

18:17.000 --> 18:18.286
Yes.

18:18.680 --> 18:20.330
(CHUCKLES) Really?

18:20.600 --> 18:22.409
Yes. Of course. Yes!

18:22.680 --> 18:23.920
(BOTH LAUGHING)

18:28.560 --> 18:29.800
(CHUCKUNG)

18:43.360 --> 18:44.964
I'm happy for you two.

18:46.040 --> 18:47.485
What are you doing here,

18:47.800 --> 18:50.280
besides destroying
the greatest moment of my life?

18:50.880 --> 18:54.407
We need to talk.
About the worst moment of mine.

18:57.360 --> 18:59.044
-(BITES AND GRUNTS)
4GROANS)

18:59.400 --> 19:00.845
MATT: Hey! Let her go.

19:03.120 --> 19:05.726
So, so sorry, officer.

19:06.320 --> 19:09.563
I found this one wandering about
and assumed she was of a

19:11.320 --> 19:12.651
drinking age.

19:14.680 --> 19:16.330
What the hell's wrong with you?

19:17.200 --> 19:19.089
Let's just say I didn't get the girl.

19:26.960 --> 19:29.566
I don't think the life-saving business
suits you, mate.

19:30.160 --> 19:33.209
Yeah, why don't you tell that to the girl
whose throat you were about to tear out.

19:34.520 --> 19:38.844
Yeah, yeah. I suppose that brings
your tally to a whopping one.

19:40.320 --> 19:43.927
Damon didn't want you.
Lily didn't want you.

19:44.560 --> 19:46.767
And this town never wanted you.

19:47.600 --> 19:49.284
So what are you still doing here?

19:52.320 --> 19:54.288
I might ask the same about you.

19:55.600 --> 19:59.400
The heretics are throwing a murder party
in your precious hometown

19:59.600 --> 20:02.809
and all you can manage to stop is my buzz.

20:05.120 --> 20:06.531
You're overmatched.

20:07.440 --> 20:11.206
You've brought a knife to a gunfight
and it's gonna be the death of you.

20:23.560 --> 20:25.210
(MUFFLED GUNSHOT)

20:25.720 --> 20:27.484
(GRUNTING)

20:34.480 --> 20:35.720
(GRUNTS)

20:44.920 --> 20:46.160
(GRUNTS)

20:53.160 --> 20:54.969
MARY: This is so typical.

20:55.280 --> 20:57.009
Nora and I have one night a year

20:57.200 --> 21:00.010
and Valerie can't stop herself
from trying to steal the spotlight.

21:00.200 --> 21:01.690
This isn't about me.

21:02.480 --> 21:03.925
It's about our family.

21:04.680 --> 21:07.206
Hold on, where's Julian?
We should wait for him.

21:07.960 --> 21:09.769
Julian won't be joining us.

21:10.880 --> 21:12.450
Hell of a party.

21:16.920 --> 21:18.410
Your mother would agree.

21:19.640 --> 21:22.450
There's a kindergarten teacher
in the powder room to prove it.

21:23.800 --> 21:25.040
Good old Mom.

21:25.280 --> 21:27.203
Bet she made you think
she enjoyed it, too.

21:27.560 --> 21:29.085
VALERIE: His face went cold.

21:30.280 --> 21:34.126
I couldn't fight him off. I couldn't...
I couldn't stop him.

21:35.600 --> 21:37.762
Julian beat me savagely.

21:38.400 --> 21:41.722
And when it was finally over
my baby was dead.

21:44.480 --> 21:46.767
Murdering my child
wasn't just some violent whim.

21:46.960 --> 21:49.930
It was a calculated, manipulative act.

21:50.440 --> 21:51.885
What are you boys doing here?

21:52.120 --> 21:53.451
It's an anniversary party.

21:53.680 --> 21:57.446
So we figured we'd come support
the pretty one and her mean girlfriend.

21:59.440 --> 22:01.169
MARY: This doesn't make sense.

22:01.480 --> 22:03.801
Why would Julian do such a thing?
What did he stand to gain?

22:04.080 --> 22:05.320
LILY; Me.

22:06.000 --> 22:10.642
I would have never gone to Europe with him
had I known about my grandchild.

22:12.800 --> 22:16.282
- Grandchild?
- Stefan was the baby's father.

22:18.120 --> 22:19.531
VALERIE: I couldn't cope.

22:20.160 --> 22:23.004
I took my own life
and became the first heretic.

22:23.960 --> 22:26.930
And when Julian saw how powerful I was,
he wanted more.

22:28.480 --> 22:32.201
We're his army, we're not his family.
We always have been.

22:33.760 --> 22:36.240
Lily, is that true?

22:37.080 --> 22:39.162
I believe every word Valerie said.

22:41.440 --> 22:43.488
When she told me what happened to her,
it was as if

22:44.200 --> 22:45.929
all the lights in the room went on.

22:48.040 --> 22:50.611
I could finally see Julian
for who he really is.

22:53.400 --> 22:56.324
That's why I'm leaving him.

22:58.520 --> 23:00.329
But she can't do it without your help.

23:01.400 --> 23:03.004
So the question is...

23:04.640 --> 23:05.926
Who do you believe?

23:23.600 --> 23:24.886
(SNIFFLES)

23:47.200 --> 23:50.682
Mare. You heard what she said.
What are you waiting for?

23:51.280 --> 23:54.329
I'm sorry. It's just...
This is a lot to take in.

23:58.200 --> 24:00.009
That's why we stick together.

24:01.520 --> 24:03.170
We're family.

24:15.120 --> 24:16.360
(SNIFFLES)

24:23.640 --> 24:25.290
Beau, give me your hand.

24:26.760 --> 24:29.206
- What is she doing?
- Bracing herself.

24:29.560 --> 24:30.800
For what?

24:35.080 --> 24:36.366
(GRUNTS)

24:36.960 --> 24:38.769
Lily, you're bleeding.

24:39.120 --> 24:40.246
(GASPS)

24:40.440 --> 24:42.249
It's about to get a lot worse.

24:42.640 --> 24:44.165
(GRUNTING)

24:48.400 --> 24:50.243
(GRUNTING)

24:51.280 --> 24:53.601
(GASPS AND PANTS)

25:01.200 --> 25:02.690
STEFAN: Let's tie him up.

25:12.560 --> 25:14.244
Damon's tying up Julian right now.

25:16.440 --> 25:17.965
I got his blood.

25:19.760 --> 25:22.650
Good. They're waiting for it
in the green house.

25:31.200 --> 25:32.645
Caroline's pregnant.

25:36.760 --> 25:39.491
Yeah, I didn't really know
what to say either.

25:41.680 --> 25:44.650
Do I even want to know how this happened?

25:46.760 --> 25:48.000
Gemini spell.

25:48.720 --> 25:49.960
Twins.

25:50.720 --> 25:52.165
Not mine, obviously.

25:53.440 --> 25:54.680
Wow.

25:55.440 --> 25:56.965
You must be overwhelmed.

25:58.560 --> 26:02.201
Well, I didn't exactly handle things
the right way.

26:04.840 --> 26:06.444
You have any advice?

26:09.760 --> 26:11.285
Tell her you love her.

26:12.360 --> 26:15.284
LILY: Never forget
what she must be going through.

26:16.160 --> 26:18.561
And then, one day...

26:20.240 --> 26:23.562
Be prepared for her
to sacrifice everything for them.

26:26.680 --> 26:28.444
Not that I'm one to give advice.

26:29.760 --> 26:32.047
I chose Julian over everything.

26:32.280 --> 26:34.044
Yeah, but now he's going to die.

26:34.960 --> 26:37.611
And you can start over without him.

26:38.880 --> 26:40.245
It's too late.

26:41.880 --> 26:45.407
- So much has already been lost.
- You haven't lost me.

26:48.880 --> 26:50.166
Really?

26:52.720 --> 26:54.006
I guessâ€œ.

26:55.240 --> 27:00.167
Willingness to forgive the unforgiveable's
in my genetics.

27:02.920 --> 27:07.926
Unfortunately, Damon doesn't feel
the same way about forgiveness.

27:09.080 --> 27:12.209
Well, you were the first woman
to break his heart.

27:13.440 --> 27:17.764
He's put up a wall ever since,
but you can take it down.

27:19.160 --> 27:20.446
No.

27:21.760 --> 27:23.046
He's gone.

27:24.560 --> 27:26.244
I saw it in his eyes.

27:27.120 --> 27:28.849
- He wishes me dead.
-(SCOFFS)

27:29.720 --> 27:32.087
Do you think that
I haven't seen that look before?

27:32.760 --> 27:37.766
Damon's been practicing that look on me
for the last 150 years.

27:38.000 --> 27:39.240
(CHUCKLES)

27:40.440 --> 27:43.922
Well, then maybe you could offer
your mother a little advice in return.

27:45.360 --> 27:46.691
How do I get him back?

27:50.600 --> 27:51.840
Time.

27:54.920 --> 27:58.970
JULIAN: My mind is boggled by this
blind devotion you have for Lily.

27:59.640 --> 28:02.883
I mean, the woman mused up an idea
to keep you away from your soul mate

28:03.080 --> 28:06.562
-for what, 60 years? 70 years?
- Stop talking.

28:06.960 --> 28:08.849
And yet, here you are,

28:09.240 --> 28:13.723
essentially risking your life to be here
with me in order to keep her alive.

28:14.160 --> 28:17.369
Don't listen to him.
He knows he's dead either way.

28:17.960 --> 28:19.564
But if he can provoke you to kill him now,

28:19.800 --> 28:22.371
then you spend eternity
as the boy who killed his own mother.

28:23.400 --> 28:24.845
Aren't you a clever girl.

28:26.480 --> 28:27.811
It's a shame...

28:28.200 --> 28:31.647
I suppose your little one would have had
the same smarts--

28:32.000 --> 28:33.240
(LAUGHS)

28:33.640 --> 28:35.608
Rot in hell, Julian.

28:38.400 --> 28:39.686
What is this?

28:39.880 --> 28:42.929
Apparently whoever wins at foosball
gets to kill me.

28:43.520 --> 28:46.967
It's pinball and I have the high score.
Did you break that link yet?

28:47.800 --> 28:50.121
How do I know that you were pregnant
with Stefan's child?

28:50.320 --> 28:51.560
Are you testing me?

28:52.280 --> 28:54.362
Do you really believe I'd make that up?

28:54.560 --> 28:56.927
You lied to Lily
about your affair with Stefan.

28:57.560 --> 28:59.608
Just like you lied to us
about killing Oscar.

29:00.040 --> 29:02.122
So why should I believe
that you're telling the truth, now?

29:02.320 --> 29:04.561
All right, Nancy Grace, enough.

29:05.360 --> 29:06.964
Let the adults handle this.

29:08.080 --> 29:09.844
-(YELLS)
- What are you doing?

29:12.440 --> 29:13.930
(GROANING)

29:15.040 --> 29:16.280
(LAUGHS)

29:16.600 --> 29:21.322
And that, Mary Louise,
is why you've always been my favorite.

29:22.040 --> 29:23.326
(EXHALES IN RELIEF)

29:29.040 --> 29:30.326
(PHONE RINGING)

29:37.400 --> 29:39.926
Well, you're either really drunk,

29:40.160 --> 29:43.607
or calling to tell me
that you found a new girlfriend.

29:45.000 --> 29:46.331
None of the above.

29:46.960 --> 29:50.407
Although a drink does sound really good
right about now.

29:50.640 --> 29:51.880
(CHUCKLES)

29:52.280 --> 29:54.089
Yeah, tell me about it.

29:55.720 --> 29:58.451
Listen, I'm really sorry about earlier.

29:59.080 --> 30:01.082
STEFAN: I didn't know what to say

30:01.440 --> 30:03.841
and I didn't want to say the wrong thing,
so I just...

30:05.320 --> 30:06.446
I bailed.

30:06.640 --> 30:10.565
Well, I guess there is no right thing
to say when you find out

30:10.800 --> 30:14.247
your girlfriend is magically pregnant
with another man's babies.

30:14.440 --> 30:15.566
(SCOFFS)

30:15.760 --> 30:19.810
CAROLINE: Look, I know that
this is happening to both of us,

30:20.600 --> 30:27.131
and you stood by me through
everything I went through with my mom.

30:28.920 --> 30:31.685
So I totally get it
if you want to run for the hills.

30:31.960 --> 30:33.803
I'm not going anywhere.

30:35.760 --> 30:37.046
Because I love you.

30:39.560 --> 30:40.971
(SIGHS IN RELIEF)

30:44.440 --> 30:47.683
I guess there is a right thing to say,
after all.

30:48.560 --> 30:52.406
Listen, no matter how weird this all gets,

30:53.800 --> 30:55.086
I'm here for you.

30:56.120 --> 30:58.043
And we're going to
get through this together.

30:58.600 --> 31:02.730
Are you sure?
'Cause it could get really weird.

31:05.040 --> 31:07.771
- I'm positive.
- Okay.

31:09.680 --> 31:11.250
And I love you, too.

31:15.480 --> 31:19.326
Mare, hey. Where are you going?
We still need to unlink Lily.

31:19.680 --> 31:21.728
- I have to get out of here.
- Mare, stop.

31:22.720 --> 31:25.121
You've been crying. What happened?

31:29.880 --> 31:31.405
Oh, my God...

31:32.320 --> 31:34.322
Things have grown out of hand, Lily.

31:34.800 --> 31:37.280
- Enough is enough.
- What are you doing? Let them go.

31:37.480 --> 31:38.720
I can't.

31:39.800 --> 31:43.122
If I do, this bloody cycle will continue.

31:44.720 --> 31:47.644
And I love you, and the family
that we have built together,

31:47.920 --> 31:49.445
far too much for that to happen.

31:50.440 --> 31:51.680
JULIAN: So.

31:52.280 --> 31:53.850
One lives, one dies.

31:54.600 --> 31:56.011
You have to choose which.

31:56.920 --> 31:58.843
- I will do no such thing.
- Oh, but you will.

32:00.000 --> 32:02.651
You have spent far too long
trying to have it all.

32:02.920 --> 32:04.843
The lies, the violence...

32:05.440 --> 32:07.522
All because you wanted the impossible.

32:08.600 --> 32:13.208
Well, the truth is, you're either
a Salvatore or you're one of us.

32:15.920 --> 32:17.684
But you cannot be both.

32:27.480 --> 32:28.686
Choose.

32:30.880 --> 32:32.120
Choose.

32:39.360 --> 32:41.203
NORA: How could you do that to Lily?

32:41.480 --> 32:43.482
How could Valerie have done
what she has to us?

32:43.800 --> 32:46.485
She hasn't been truthful
about anything, Nora.

32:46.720 --> 32:49.883
Her relationship with Stefan? Lies.
Killing Oscar? More lies.

32:50.200 --> 32:52.362
- This is different.
- Of course you would think that.

32:52.640 --> 32:56.167
He took her child from her.
And you would side with him?

32:56.360 --> 32:58.567
And you would side with the girl
who murdered her own brother?

33:05.080 --> 33:07.890
- No. What are you doing?
- This doesn't represent our love.

33:08.320 --> 33:10.163
It represents Julian's ability
to manipulate us.

33:10.480 --> 33:11.845
- I don't want it.
- Nora, please. Don't--

33:12.040 --> 33:15.169
- I don't want any of it.
- Nora. Nora!

33:16.480 --> 33:17.845
This isn't you.

33:19.840 --> 33:23.083
This is not the man
that I fell in love with.

33:24.760 --> 33:28.765
LILY: You used to be kind. Gentle. Funny.

33:29.680 --> 33:31.170
No, no, you...

33:31.560 --> 33:35.770
You're still in shock from the hell
that you've been trapped in for so long...

33:36.000 --> 33:38.128
Hell didn't turn him evil, Lily.

33:38.600 --> 33:40.887
- He was born this way.
- Okay...

33:41.200 --> 33:42.531
This vervain stings like a bitch

33:42.720 --> 33:46.122
and your family drama makes
the prospect of hell look like Disneyland.

33:46.920 --> 33:51.608
So, please, one swift stab.
Straight through the heart.

33:53.040 --> 33:54.963
Let's get this over with.

33:56.080 --> 33:59.129
You chose your heretics over
Stefan and me every chance you've had.

33:59.360 --> 34:00.771
Why stop now?

34:01.240 --> 34:02.890
Lily, please...

34:05.800 --> 34:07.802
LILY: You are such a strong girl.

34:10.280 --> 34:12.806
I am so sorry I didn't see it sooner.

34:21.280 --> 34:23.487
My son.

34:24.920 --> 34:26.159
Please forgive me.

34:28.159 --> 34:29.571
Kill me.

34:30.560 --> 34:33.245
Come on, do it, Lily.

34:33.639 --> 34:36.085
You're wrong about so many things.

34:38.120 --> 34:40.804
I never had the courage
to tell you before,

34:42.600 --> 34:43.840
but I do now.

34:45.920 --> 34:49.447
You are wrong, Julian...

34:53.440 --> 34:55.681
I can choose them both.

34:58.000 --> 34:59.206
(GASPS)

34:59.440 --> 35:00.965
No, Lily!

35:01.840 --> 35:03.604
- Lily!
-(PANTING)

35:04.600 --> 35:06.125
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

35:07.000 --> 35:10.527
My sweet, foolish girl.
I've already unlinked us.

35:10.840 --> 35:12.126
(GASPS)

35:15.880 --> 35:17.530
- No.
- Lily.

35:18.160 --> 35:19.889
(WHIMPERING)

35:36.560 --> 35:37.891
Save your strength.

35:38.120 --> 35:39.246
You're full of vervain

35:39.400 --> 35:41.129
and you couldn't break out of here
on your best day.

35:41.400 --> 35:43.402
- What the hell did you do?
- I took your advice.

35:44.160 --> 35:45.491
You see, you're right.

35:46.080 --> 35:50.563
I can't protect Mystic Falls on my own
so I made some friends who could help.

35:52.400 --> 35:55.722
- And who are these friends?
- Sorry, I can't tell you.

35:56.520 --> 35:58.249
See, they'd like to introduce themselves.

35:58.680 --> 36:01.889
I guess I was wrong.
Someone wanted you, after all.

36:02.480 --> 36:03.766
(CLANGING)

36:10.080 --> 36:13.209
The splinters must be inside your heart...
I can't get them out!

36:14.080 --> 36:15.366
Nora...

36:16.200 --> 36:17.440
It's all right...

36:18.560 --> 36:20.927
What do I do? Tell me what to do.

36:23.600 --> 36:25.204
You say goodbye.

36:34.920 --> 36:37.207
We wouldn't be a family without you, Lily.

36:37.960 --> 36:41.567
I love you. I am so sorry this happened.

36:49.040 --> 36:50.280
Goodbye.

37:05.040 --> 37:06.326
(SIGHS)

37:28.160 --> 37:31.084
I guess only one of us

37:32.840 --> 37:34.683
gets the luxury of time.

37:40.440 --> 37:44.081
Promise me
you'll use yours to the fullest.

38:00.040 --> 38:02.884
-(YELLING)
-(SHATTERING)

38:05.160 --> 38:07.049
Nora gave me back the ring.

38:10.480 --> 38:11.811
What is all this?

38:15.200 --> 38:16.486
JULIAN: Lily...

38:19.160 --> 38:21.128
She staked herself in the heart.

38:22.960 --> 38:24.007
What?

38:24.160 --> 38:26.731
She thought that killing herself
would kill me.

38:27.840 --> 38:30.730
She didn't realize
that you had already unlinked us.

38:32.560 --> 38:35.040
I thought breaking the spell
would protect her.

38:35.680 --> 38:37.808
If her sons succeeded in killing me,

38:39.040 --> 38:40.326
she would be spared.

38:40.920 --> 38:42.410
But instead...

38:42.840 --> 38:44.569
No. Tell me this isn't real.

38:45.080 --> 38:48.926
- Tell me this isn't happening!
- She's gone, Mary Louise. She's gone!

38:50.240 --> 38:51.480
(GASPS)

39:00.600 --> 39:02.568
VALERIE: I forgive you for
loving him, Lily.

39:04.520 --> 39:06.170
You just wanted to love us all.

39:07.280 --> 39:08.850
There is no sin in that.

39:20.280 --> 39:22.044
She only has moments left.

39:22.920 --> 39:24.365
Make the most of them.

39:42.440 --> 39:43.646
Damon...

39:48.560 --> 39:50.403
LILY: I'm truly sorry.

39:59.240 --> 40:00.480
Say something.

40:09.560 --> 40:10.846
(EXHALES)

40:12.920 --> 40:14.649
You made your bed.

40:17.000 --> 40:18.286
Have a nice nap.

40:44.000 --> 40:45.365
Mom?

40:45.600 --> 40:46.965
(FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING)

40:47.360 --> 40:49.010
Are you still here?

40:51.840 --> 40:53.490
-(CHAINS CLINK)
%GROANS)

40:56.960 --> 41:00.282
I'm so sorry.
I don't think I can save you.

41:01.640 --> 41:03.802
You've been poisoned with werewolf toxin.

41:05.120 --> 41:08.363
Without proper treatment, you'll die soon.

41:12.320 --> 41:13.810
Okay, Mom, listen.

41:14.520 --> 41:16.010
While you're still here,

41:16.800 --> 41:19.167
there's something
that's been nagging at me

41:20.520 --> 41:21.885
for a long time.

41:27.000 --> 41:28.570
I'm so sorry.

41:29.880 --> 41:31.086
(SCOFFS)

41:32.000 --> 41:33.331
Mom?

41:33.560 --> 41:34.891
Wow!

41:35.320 --> 41:37.322
You must really be having a bad trip.

41:38.680 --> 41:40.762
Your mother's been dead for years.

41:43.520 --> 41:45.010
You're not my mother.

41:45.880 --> 41:47.086
(GRUNTS)

41:53.600 --> 41:55.921
(CLOSING MUSIC PLAYING)

42:17.920 --> 42:18.967
English - SDH
